Welcome to Ranabir Janahit Secondary School

Established in 1963 AD, Ranabir Janahit Secondary School (रणविर जनहित माध्यामिक विद्यालय) has been a beacon of education in Waling for over 60 years. Located in Waling Municipality-1, Khahare, Syangja, Gandaki Province, we are a distinguished public academic institution with triple affiliations: National Examination Board (NEB), Ministry of Education (MoE), and Council for Technical Education and Vocational Training (CTEVT).

We offer comprehensive education from Grade 1 to 12, Ten Plus Two (+2) programs in Management and Education streams, and specialized CTEVT-approved technical programs including Diploma in Electrical Engineering and Pre-Diploma (Electrical Sub-overseer). Our mission is clear: ensuring no local student remains unemployed by providing access to quality education, vocational training, and preparing a skilled workforce and competent leaders for Nepal's development.
